This paper deals with evidential reasoning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of conditional belief functions is a technique commonly used in machine learning and probabilistic reasoning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses propagation algorithms, which are commonly used in network analysis and optimization, falling under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The analysis of special evidential networks also involves the study of their properties and structures, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the representation of relations among variables, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
